The paper deals with social network algorithms and influence maximization, which are topics that fall under the categories of social networks (cs.SOC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper specifically mentions the computational social sciences, which is a subfield of computer science that focuses on the application of computational methods to social science research, and thus falls under the category of social and information sciences (cs.SI).
